{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 18:41:23.283271", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Anomaly detected: the 10.0.1.0/24 leaf subnet (pc_0_1 behind leaf_router_0_1) is not being advertised into the EBGP fabric. As a result, traffic destined to 10.0.1.0/24 from elsewhere in the DC is unreachable.\\n- Overall fabric health: EBGP sessions are up across the fabric and other subnets are reachable; the issue is localized to leaf_router_0_1’s missing origination of its directly connected host subnet.\\n\\nObserved Symptoms\\n- End-to-end reachability:\\n  - pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2): 100% loss with “From 10.0.0.1 Destination Net Unreachable”.\\n  - Many other host-to-host pings succeed (e.g., to 10.0.0.2/10.0.3.2).\\n  - Reachability tool shows unknown for tests targeting pc_0_1, suggesting wider fabric cannot reach its subnet.\\n- Local connectivity:\\n  - On pc_0_1, default route is via 10.0.1.1 and ping to gateway succeeds:\\n    - ip route: default via 10.0.1.1 dev eth0; 10.0.1.0/24 dev eth0\\n    - ping 10.0.1.1: OK\\n\\nControl-Plane Findings\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201):\\n  - Interfaces: eth4 = 10.0.1.1/24 (connected to pc_0_1)\\n  - EBGP sessions to spines are established (4 neighbors, PfxRcd=7 each).\\n  - RIB: 10.0.1.0/24 is connected, but not present in BGP table.\\n    - show ip bgp: lists multiple 10.x.x.0/24 networks from upstream; does NOT include 10.0.1.0/24.\\n    - show running-config: router bgp 65201 has neighbor statements but no “network 10.0.1.0/24” and no “redistribute connected”.\\n    - show ip bgp neighbors 172.16.0.34 advertised-routes: advertises several prefixes, but NOT 10.0.1.0/24.\\n- Downstream devices do not have route to 10.0.1.0/24:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 and spines:\\n    - show ip bgp 10.0.1.0/24: “% Network not in table”.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 bgp summary:\\n    - Neighbor 172.16.0.35 (leaf_router_0_1) PfxRcd=0, indicating spine receives no usable prefixes from leaf_router_0_1.\\n\\nData-Plane Corroboration\\n- pc_0_0 → 10.0.1.2 fails with ICMP Net Unreachable from 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0 gateway), consistent with the absence of a route to 10.0.1.0/24 in the fabric.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty device: leaf_router_0_1\\n- Faulty plane: Control plane (BGP route origination)\\n- Evidence:\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 has the 10.0.1.1/24 interface up and can serve its host locally.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 does not originate 10.0.1.0/24 into BGP (no network statement/redistribution), so upstream routers have no route to the subnet.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_1 FRR BGP: the directly connected host subnet 10.0.1.0/24 is not injected into BGP (missing “network 10.0.1.0/24” or equivalent redistribution), preventing propagation to spines/superspine and leaving the rest of the fabric without a route to pc_0_1’s network.\\n\\nImpact Assessment\\n- All traffic destined to the 10.0.1.0/24 subnet from other racks/pods is unreachable.\\n- Other subnets (e.g., 10.0.0.0/24, 10.0.2.0/24, 10.0.3.0/24, 10.1.x.0/24) appear reachable across the fabric.\\n- Traffic sourced from 10.0.1.0/24 to other subnets may forward out from leaf_router_0_1 (it has BGP routes), but return traffic will fail due to missing reverse route, resulting in end-to-end failures., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='bbfc8cc1-9784-474f-baa1-104e5ed014b8'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
